cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a defense strategy against adversarial attacks on deep learning models, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing defense methods, which can be considered as a contribution to the sub-field of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the proposed defense strategy involves the use of Langevin dynamics, which is a common technique in the sub-field of neural networks (cs.NE).
